sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Wild type plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter with mRFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum, iGEM part registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter composite part includes mRFP reporter (BBa_E1010). After co-transformation with light sensor BBa_K1913033, mRFP fluorescence could be detected after 12h culture.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to test wild type plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter,we put reporter mRFP under this promoter and co-transformed with light sensor BBa_K1913034. And mRFP fluorescence value was tested so that the intensity of transcription of this promoter could be quantified.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Double terminator consisting of BBa_B0010 and BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1913025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Wild type plac-FixK2 hybrid promoter is the promoter that could not only be activated by light sensorsYF1-FixJ composite and but inhibited by LacI repressor. The sequence of upper control element and core element region are from wild type FixK2 hybrid promoter on genomic sequence of Bradyrhizobium japonicum. Addition lac operators on the both side of promoter as second control element that results in transcription repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: In order to make Fixk2 promoter as an inducible promoter for the toggle switch,we had to add additional repressor operator sequences into the Fixk2 sequence, they are both on upstream and downstream the Fixk2 sequence, which could be bonded by tetrameric Lac repressor resulting in the formation of a DNA loop and consequently on transcription repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg
